# C/C++ Systems Standards

Apply these rules when editing C/C++ in controller, server, proxy, or sensor.

- Use RAII and smart pointers (`std::unique_ptr`, `std::shared_ptr`); avoid raw
  `new/delete`.
- Keep naming consistent: `PascalCase` for classes, `snake_case` for methods
  and variables, `kUpperCase` for constants.
- Use `#pragma once` in headers.
- Keep processes decoupled and preserve the communication boundaries between
  `sensor`, `proxy`, `server`, and `controller`.
- Use project logging conventions consistently so runtime traces are useful for
  system validation and debugging.

## Testing Requirements

- If C++ logic changes, update/add corresponding Google Test coverage in
  `tests/gtests/`.
- If the change affects process interaction, add or update a Robot Framework
  integration test in `tests/robot/`.
- Treat missing tests as incomplete work.
